dcterms:description: WikiTableQuestions (WikiTQ) contains relational tables with relatively simple structures, collected from Wikipedia articles. The questions usually involve basic arithmetic operations and sometimes require compositional reasoning over table entries.
dcterms:title: WikiTableQuestions (WikiTQ)

dcterms:description: HiTab involves hierarchical matrix tables collected from statistical reports and Wikipedia articles, covering diverse domains such as economics, education, health, and science. It challenges existing methods with its broad set of operations and complex table structures.
dcterms:title: HiTab

dcterms:description: AIT-QA contains tables and questions that focus on the airline industry domain, featuring complex structures such as hierarchical headers or bi-dimensional matrix shapes. It presents challenges due to its domain-specific terminology.
dcterms:title: AIT-QA

dcterms:description: Spider is a multi-domain text-to-SQL benchmark with tables in a database format, containing 200 databases across 138 different domains. It poses unique challenges due to its multi-table structure.
